</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Gun control</h1>
						<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p><b>Gun control</b> generally refers to laws or policies that regulate the manufacture, sale, transfer, possession, modification, or use of <a href="/wiki/Firearm" title="Firearm">firearms</a>. They vary greatly around the world. Some countries, such as the <a href="/wiki/Gun_politics_in_the_United_Kingdom" title="Gun politics in the United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>, have very strict limits on gun possession while others, like the <a href="/wiki/Gun_politics_in_the_United_States" title="Gun politics in the United States">United States</a>, have, compared to most industrial democracies, relatively few and weak restrictions (although policies vary from state to state).</p>
<p>Proponents of gun control generally argue that widespread gun ownership increases the danger of homicide and suicide. Opponents argue that gun control does not reduce gun-related injuries, murder, or suicide, and some argue that certain regulations may violate individual liberties.</p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
